peddler /ˈpɛdlə/

(peddlers) 

1. N-COUNT [美国英语] →see pedlar 

2. N-COUNT A drug peddler is a person who sells illegal drugs. 毒贩 

3. N-COUNT A peddler of information or ideas is someone who frequently expresses such ideas to other people. 宣扬者; 散布者 [usu N 'of' n] [表不满] 

例： ...the peddlers of fear. ...恐惧的散布者。

